## 🐛 Bug Report

<!-- A clear and concise description of what the bug is. -->

Lib version: 4.3.0

## Steps To Reproduce

<!-- The exact steps required to reproduce the issue, ideally with a code example -->

```javascript

 async function test() {
  const wb = new ExcelJS.Workbook();
  const ws = wb.addWorksheet('Sheet 1');
  const headerFont = { bold: true };
  ws.columns = [
    { key: 'id', header: 'ID', style: { font: headerFont } },
    { key: 'name', header: 'Name', style: { font: headerFont } },
  ];

  [
    { id: '1', name: 'First' },
    { id: '2', name: 'Second' },
  ].forEach((record, index) => {
    const row = ws.addRow(record);
    row.outlineLevel = index + 1;
    row.getCell(1).note = 'some notes';
  });

  // The above works fine until the following codes are added

  ws.insertRow(1, ['1', '1']);
  ws.mergeCells(1, 1, 1, 2);

  await wb.xlsx.writeFile('./test.xlsx');
}
```
- The outline level is wrong (not shifted accordingly) after a new row inserted.
- The notes disappears after a new row inserted.

## The expected behaviour:

<!-- A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen. -->

The row outline level and cell notes should be properly persisted after `worksheet.insertRow(1)` call. I did this because I'd like to show some merged cells on top row.
